// TEST: unknown_method_concrete
// EXPECT: error E4013 at 16:19
//
// Q-checker-unknown-method-concrete: an unknown method on a CONCRETE receiver
// is a checker error (`E4013`), not a silent resolution to a fresh type
// variable (which would pass `bock check` yet emit no/garbage codegen — the
// general form of the DQ22 `Map.contains` soundness hole). Here `List[Int]` is
// a fully-resolved built-in receiver and `frobnicate` is in none of its method
// sets, so the call is rejected. A near-name typo additionally gets a "did you
// mean `…`?" note (see `xs.lenght()` in the checker unit tests); `frobnicate`
// is far from every List method, so no suggestion is offered here.
module main

fn main() -> Void {
  let xs: List[Int] = [1, 2, 3]
  let n: Int = xs.frobnicate()
  println("${n}")
}
